    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2009-01-06</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2009-01-15T21:09:22Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Bad Polluters Act of 2009- Amends the Internal Revenue Code to deny to a Great Lakes polluter the taxpayer election to expense 50% of the cost of refinery property in the current taxpayer year. Defines &quot;Great Lakes polluter&quot; as a refinery owner that holds a permit issued by the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) to discharge a certain level of pollutants into the Great Lakes.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
